mnumber 293
ADJECTIVE 165
name litch
*DESCRIPTION_START
The sekleth litch looks much like an oversized, hulking drakin with two heads.
It stinks with the odor of the grave, but its reptilian flesh remains dry and
well preserved. It is adorned with a rotting shroud of unknown material and
carries a bone sceptre inlaid with otherworldly jewels. You are sure you are
looking upon an unknowably old creature, a remnant of a past aeon when the
sekleth were mighty upon Andor. Its blank gaze echos nothing of what dark
secrets might be contained within its fossilized skull.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ARMOR 80
ATTACK1 200
BODY 250
DEFENSE 150
DISCORPORATE
DISEASE 20 10
EXTRABODY 50
